dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-gdi7,related,"2026-07-10T16:39:25.446Z",null,null
body: "## Problem\nWhen a command fails due to a missing boolean flag, the recovery bundle's suggested_retry appends a \"<value>\" placeholder to the flag. Boolean flags take no value, so running the suggested command verbatim fails with a different error (too many arguments). Agents are the primary consumers of suggested_retry and copy it verbatim — an executable-looking suggestion that errors when followed burns a round-trip and erodes trust in the recovery bundle.\n\n## Repro (pm 2026.7.10)\npm close <id> done on an already-terminal item -> missing: --force -> suggested_retry: pm close <id> done --force \"<value>\" -> running it: too many arguments for 'close'.\n\n## Fix direction\nThe suggested_retry renderer must consult each flag's arity from the flag contract: arity-0 flags rendered bare, value flags with a typed placeholder. Related territory: pm-gdi7 owns unknown-option suggestion polish in the same envelope layer; this is the retry-renderer half.\n\n## Philosophy tie-in\nproject management = context management — recovery bundles are agent context; they must be executable as-is.\n\n## Source\nhttps://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/500"
